      "solution": "from collections import Counter\n\ns = input()\n\n# Count every chars in the string\nc = Counter(s)\n\nresult = ''\nfor i in s:\n    # get the  alphabet position + the number of occurences of the letter\n    aplhabet_position = ord(i)+ c[i] - ord('a')\n    \n    #dont let it make it past the alphabet\n    aplhabet_position = ord('a') + (aplhabet_position % 26)\n\n    #transform the new alphabet_position back to a char and append it to the result\n    result += chr(aplhabet_position)\nprint(result)",
